# Cursor Agent Rules — IgorOpenClaw

## What this repo is

This is NOT a software application. It is the **configuration and workspace
repository** for an OpenClaw autonomous AI agent running on a Mac Mini M2
(Apple Silicon, 8 GB RAM, macOS).

OpenClaw is installed globally via npm (`npm install -g openclaw`). This repo
contains:

- `config/openclaw.json.template` — main OpenClaw configuration template (secrets
  injected from `.env` by `scripts/setup.sh` into `~/.openclaw/openclaw.json` —
  generated file is git-ignored)
- `config/riley-voice-behavior.md` — canonical Vapi assistant voicemail + callback policy (merge into Riley’s system prompt)
- `workspace/` — OpenClaw agent workspace files (AGENTS.md, SOUL.md, etc.),
  symlinked into `~/.openclaw/workspace/`
- `scripts/` — setup, teardown, and integration helpers (imessage.py, whatsapp.py,
  vapi-call.py, setup.sh, uninstall.sh)
- `SETUP_GUIDE.md` — full installation walkthrough

## Critical rules

1. **Never commit secrets.** All API keys live in `.env` (git-ignored). Config
   files reference them via environment variable names only.
2. **Never hardcode API keys, tokens, or passwords** in any file that gets
   committed.
3. **After editing `config/openclaw.json.template`** (then re-run `setup.sh`) **or**
   **`~/.openclaw/openclaw.json`**, restart the gateway: `openclaw gateway restart`.
4. **After editing any `workspace/*.md` file**, changes take effect on the
   agent's next turn (no restart needed).
5. **SETUP_GUIDE.md is a standalone doc** meant to be pasted into a Gemini
   session. Keep it self-contained with full commands and context.

## File layout

- `config/openclaw.json.template` — multi-model config template (OpenAI primary,
  Gemini fallback), WhatsApp channel, security settings. Auth token placeholder
  `__OPENCLAW_AUTH_TOKEN__` is injected from `.env` at setup time.
- `config/cron/jobs.json` — scheduled/heartbeat job definitions
- `workspace/AGENTS.md` — operational rules, task routing, and **Questions to the user** (prefer y/n and multiple choice when practical)
- `workspace/SOUL.md` — agent personality and tone
- `workspace/USER.md` — user context (timezone, preferences)
- `workspace/TOOLS.md` — available tools and environment notes
- `workspace/MEMORY.md` — agent persistent state (active tasks, completed log,
  learned patterns, corrections)
- `workspace/HEARTBEAT.md` — proactive behavior guidelines (references
  config/cron/jobs.json for schedules)
- `.env.example` — template for required environment variables

## After every change session

1. **Update documentation.** Any change you make — config, scripts, workspace
   files, new skills — must be reflected in the relevant docs:
   - `README.md` — project overview, architecture, repo layout, quick start
   - `SETUP_GUIDE.md` — self-contained installation walkthrough (for Gemini)
   - `.cursorrules` (this file) — file layout, rules, and conventions
   - `workspace/*.md` — if agent behavior or tools changed
   Keep docs accurate so that a **fresh Cursor agent session** (with no memory
   of prior conversations) can understand the full project state by reading them.

2. **Commit and push to GitHub.** After completing changes, stage, commit, and
   push so nothing is lost:
   ```bash
   git add .
   git commit -m "<concise description of what changed and why>"
   git push
   ```
   Never commit `.env` or any file containing secrets.

3. **Restart if needed.** After editing `config/openclaw.json.template` / live
   `~/.openclaw/openclaw.json` or `scripts/`:
   ```bash
   openclaw gateway restart
   ```

## Testing changes

```bash
# Restart gateway after config changes
openclaw gateway restart

# Check gateway health
openclaw gateway status

# View recent logs (rotated daily)
ls -lt /tmp/openclaw/openclaw-*.log | head -3
tail -50 /tmp/openclaw/openclaw-$(date +%Y-%m-%d).log
```

## Current state snapshot

Keep this section updated after every change session.

- **Primary model:** openai/gpt-5.4
- **Fallback model:** google/gemini-2.5-pro
- **WhatsApp:** allowlist-only (owner +19179752041, +19176997436), groups disabled
- **Gateway:** localhost:18789, token auth (token injected from .env via template)
- **Browser:** dedicated Chrome debug profile at ~/.openclaw/chrome-profile/ (port 9222)
- **Daily restart:** 4 AM ET via launchd (ai.openclaw.daily-restart), restarts
  Chrome debug profile + gateway
- **Cron jobs:** post-restart-resume (4:05 AM), morning briefing (7:30 AM),
  api-spend-check (5:00 AM — OpenAI+Vapi last-24h $ + Cursor plan status → WhatsApp; uses OPENAI_ADMIN_KEY; reads Cursor token from local SQLite),
  email triage (every 2h 8AM-10PM), chrono24-listing-monitor (5× daily if MEMORY
  has Chrono24 task), sms-reply-monitor (~every 2h 8:30AM–8:30PM ET, **sms-watch**),
  inbound call check (every 30 min), system health (every 6h). Browser-using
  crons must end with **browser close** (AGENTS.md § Browser hygiene).
- **Task persistence:** ongoing tasks written to MEMORY.md → Active Tasks with
  TTL (default 7 days), explicit done-when criteria, 48h staleness rule.
  See AGENTS.md § Task Persistence for full rules.
- **Skills installed (17 ready):**
  - ClawHub: browser-automation, screenshot
  - Bundled: coding-agent, gemini, github, gh-issues, peekaboo, summarize,
    healthcheck, openai-image-gen, openai-whisper-api, weather, skill-creator,
    node-connect
  - Newly added: gog (Google Workspace), himalaya (email IMAP/SMTP),
    apple-reminders (remindctl)
- **iMessage/SMS:** scripts/imessage.py (reads chat.db, sends via AppleScript).
  Requires Full Disk Access for python3 binary. Read=autonomous, send=ask user.
- **Phone calls:** scripts/vapi-call.py (outbound + inbound via Vapi AI).
  Voice agent "Riley" (assistant ID in VAPI_ASSISTANT_ID env var).
  Outbound number: +19179628631. Fallback: +19179752041 (Igor's cell).
  Always ask user before dialing outbound; ask whether Riley may leave a callback
  number on voicemail, and encode YES/NO in the task string (see TOOLS.md).
  Cost ~11¢/min.
  Inbound calls auto-answered by Riley (takes messages, blocks spam).
  Inbound polling: cron every 30 min → vapi-call.py inbound-check → WhatsApp alert.
  Voicemail/callback policy: `config/riley-voice-behavior.md` + per-call injection in `vapi-call.py`.
  See TOOLS.md § Phone Calls for full architecture and troubleshooting.
- **Email:** himalaya CLI (IMAP/SMTP with Gmail app password) + gog gmail (OAuth)
- **Calendar/Drive/Contacts:** gog CLI (OAuth, project polar-city-407401)
- **User questions:** When Clawd needs a decision or missing info from Igor, prefer **yes/no** or **multiple-choice** (A/B/C) when it fits; don’t force when only open-ended works. See `workspace/AGENTS.md` § Questions to the user.
- **GitHub:** https://github.com/iarsenin/IgorOpenClaw (private)
